{
  "text": "The process that changes one DC voltage to a different DC voltage is called DC-DC conversion. A boost converter is a DC-DC power converter that steps up the input voltage to a higher output (load) voltage [CITATION_1] . It is a converter which consists of two semiconductors (a diode and a transistor) and one energy storage element inductor. To reduce voltage ripple, filters made of capacitors are normally added to such a converter's output (load-side filter). For DC-DC boost converter the relationship between input voltage and output voltage is",
